      "raw_text": "A resolution providing that when\nthe government advances an irri-\ncation project in a locality In which\nIa private irrigation concern has\nstarted such project, the govern\nment should reimburse the private\nconcern for all expense 1t has In\nCured, was flatly turned down by\nthe irrigation congress this after\nnoon.\n\n\nThe resolution was offered BY\nthe resolution committee at the In\nstance of parties believed to be in\nterested in private irrigation pro-\nject in Arizona. The proposition\nseemed to meet with the approval\nof no one of the regular delegates\nat the convention, as the interests\nof promoters OF private irrigation\nprojects was shown too plainly on\nthe surface."
